cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a supervised learning approach, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of random forests for regression also suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for saliency detection, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
